=== Sprint 2 · Task S2.3: GetAccountStatus / VerifyTradePermission → real ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §4.S2.3

--- Problem ---
V2 §2.D-3 / plan S2.3: Both GetAccountStatus and VerifyTradePermission returned
hardcoded responses that always indicated success regardless of actual account state.

- GetAccountStatus: always returned {State: "connected", LastTickAt: now()} with no
  ownership check, session check, or PG status check.
- VerifyTradePermission: always returned {HasTradePermission: true, Verified: true}
  after only checking the account exists in PG (no disabled/frozen/status check).

--- Fix ---
Part 1 — internal/mthub/service.go (MODIFIED):
- Added SessionState(ctx, accountID) method to MtHubService
- Uses Hub.EnsureSession (auto-refreshes expired sessions)
- Returns "connected" or "not_found"

Part 2 — internal/connect/system/mthub_service.go (MODIFIED):
- GetAccountStatus now checks:
  a. User authentication (GetUserID)
  b. Ownership: platform.GetAccount(ctx, userID, accountID) with WHERE user_id=$2
  c. Hub session state via svc.SessionState()
  d. Falls back to PG account_status if no session found
- Added uuid import for user ID parsing

Part 3 — internal/connect/user/account_handler.go (MODIFIED):
- VerifyTradePermission now checks:
  a. Account exists and belongs to user (existing GetAccount check)
  b. acct.IsDisabled → returns HasTradePermission: false, "account is disabled"
  c. acct.Status == "frozen" or "needs_rebind" → returns false with reason
  d. Otherwise → returns true

Part 4 — internal/mthub/session_test.go (NEW):
- TestSessionState_Connected: registered session → "connected"
- TestSessionState_NotFound: no session → "not_found"
- TestSessionState_ExpiredRefreshes: expired session auto-refreshed → "connected"

